LOS ANGELES — The life of the late rapper Mac Miller was remembered with a benefit concert at the Greek Theatre in Los Angeles on Wednesday, with the aim of raising funds for arts education in underserved communities. Chance the Rapper, John Mayer and SZA performed at the “Mac Miller: A Celebration of Life” concert. Paramedics found the 26-year-old Miller unresponsive in his home last month and declared him dead soon after. No cause of death has been announced after an autopsy was performed. Miller’s rhymes often dealt with his depression and drug use. The lineup included Travis Scott, Miguel, Ty Dolla $ign, ScHoolboy Q, Anderson .Paak, Earl Sweatshirt, Vince Staples and Action Bronson.  (AP)